window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>After Thomas defeated the Bloodfallen, he thought everything was over. However, when the Goddess herself sent him a vision of an army of monsters approaching the kingdom, he knew that he had to take action.</p> <p>Assembling an elite squad of people he could awaken the powers of wasn’t something he thought he would do, but he found himself needing to do just that. After testing out his power to awaken the potential of sorceresses on Sophia and Veronica, he decided that the best way to find talent and earn some money at the same time was by…opening a gym!</p> <p>However, he had no time to breathe, as, after the queen summoned him and informed Thomas that he were to lead an entire battalion, he could no longer stay at the academy.</p> <p>Under the guidance of Hera Perkar—the legendary army commander—He set forth alongside his squad toward Veronica’s estate to begin preparation for a war bigger than himself.</p>"; 
